news.title: Builder associations in Maharashtra seek reduction of stamp duty to 3%
news.para: State revenue officials, however, believe reducing stamp duty is improbable due to existing budget allocations and ongoing welfare schemes, with the department playing a key role in contributing to the state exchequer.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body rejects proposal to align house tax with circle rate
news.para: "Despite councillors opposing the hike, GMC had been sending notices arbitrarily, demanding house tax akigned with the DM circle rate. The GMC board on Saturday, however, struck down the proposal. The consumers can breathe easy," said Mayor Sunita Dayal.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body releases 2.2 million draft e-khatas online
news.para: “Unlike other metros, we at BBMP have maintained ownership records. In many states, property ownership is handled by the Revenue department, but in Bengaluru, the city corporation is maintaining it,” BBMP Special Commissioner (Revenue) Munish Moudgil told ET.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC auctions builder's cars to recover Rs 14 crore property tax dues
news.para: Following the e-auction, BMC received around Rs 10 lakh for the three cars of which about Rs 1.5 lakh was adjusted to the auction charges, while the remaining sum was adjusted to the pending dues of the developer.

news.title: Tellado Realty divests its hospitality business to StayVista
news.para: StayVista said it will be making its fully-serviced stays available at Tellado’s villa establishments in Assagao, Siolim, Mandrem and Aldona.

news.title: About 1.9 lakh apply for 361 residential plots near Noida airport
news.para: Launched in July this year, YEIDA's latest scheme includes residential plots in sectors 16, 18, 20 and 22D. The plot sizes range from 120sqm to 4,000sqm, and are priced at Rs 29,500 per sqm.

news.title: Garuda Construction IPO subscribed 4.1 times on October 9
news.para: The portion meant for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) got subscribed 6.73 times while the quota for non-institutional investors received 2.58 times subscription.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to jointly develop a residential project in Bengaluru
news.para: The project has a total estimated saleable area of 4.2 lakh sq ft and a top-line potential of Rs 600 crore.

news.title: Goa: FIR filed over forged papers for sale deed of seven flats
news.para: Pernem PI Sachin Lokre said that the accused hatched a conspiracy and, with common intent, prepared forged board resolutions of the complainant’s company, Eco Promoters Pvt Ltd.

news.title: NeoLiv acquires 12 acres land to develop mixed-use villas in Alibaug
news.para: The development, with an option to extend to 20 acres, has projected gross development value of more than Rs 400 crore.

news.title: Mussoorie civic body issues demolition notices to 17 buildings
news.para: The owners of these buildings have been instructed to commence the demolition process by Oct 14, according to the notice. Officials said that the notices were issued based on National Green Tribunal (NGT) orders issued in 2023 following landslides in Landour.

news.title: Bengaluru metro to introduce multimodal connectivity systems at 11 phase-III stations
news.para: Phase 3 will include two corridors: one connecting JP Nagar 4th Phase to Kempapura (32 km) and another connecting Hosahalli to Kadabagere (13 km), with 22 and 9 stations respectively.

news.title: Delhi mayor launches ward-wise action to address C&D waste
news.para: The mayor highlighted that illegal dumping near construction sites, on roadsides, and behind houses inside colonies had become a common practice, contributing significantly to dust pollution in Delhi.

news.title: Central government launches survey to identify new rural housing beneficiaries
news.para: The survey will be completed within six months and those living in kutcha dwelling units could qualify for pucca (all-weather) houses under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana-Gramin (PMAY-G), he added.

news.title: Cement firms' profits likely to halve in Q2 FY25
news.para: The September quarter is generally weak for cement producers as demand is lower on account of the monsoon rains, which slows down construction activities.

news.title: NCLT directs to initiate insolvency proceedings against Syska LED Lights
news.para: The Mumbai bench of NCLT admitted the plea filed by Sunstar Industries, claiming total dues of Rs 7.70 crore and has appointed Debashis Nanda as the interim resolution professional suspending the board of Syska LED Lights, as per the provisions of the Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code (IBC).

news.title: Delhi civic body launches C&D waste removal drive to tackle winter pollution
news.para: A meeting was held a few days back and it was decided that a special drive will be launched to ensure that deputy and assistant commissioners conduct daily inspections in Delhi's 12 zones, Oberoi said.

news.title: Jaipur development body demolishes seven illegal colonies
news.para: Officials said that the first colony was being developed on around two bighas of private agricultural land in the Vatika village on Neemdi Road. The second colony was being established on an eight bigha private agricultural land in Simliya village.

news.title: RBI's monetary policy committee changes policy stance to 'neutral'
news.para: The monetary policy committee, which included three RBI officials and an equal number of new external members, voted five-to-one to keep the benchmark repurchase or repo rate - which governs the interest rate of home, auto, corporate and other loans - at 6.5 per cent for a 10th straight policy meeting.
